snippet: The bill would have allowed biosimilar versions of biologic drugs to be substituted by pharmacists if the F.D.A. deemed them “interchangeable” with the reference product.
abstract: California Gov Jerry Brown vetoes bill that would have allowed biosimilar versions of biologic drugs to be substituted by pharmacists if Food and Drug Administration deemed them 'interchangeable' with the brand-name reference product.
lead_paragraph: The bill would have allowed biosimilar versions of biologic drugs to be substituted by pharmacists if the F.D.A. deemed them “interchangeable” with the reference product.

headline.main: Gov. Brown of California Vetoes Biotech Drug Bill
headline.print_headline: Gov. Brown of California Vetoes Biotech Drug Bill
